The Proposal:
P. R. Pote Patil International School, Amravati run by Maratha Education Institute, Ashtati, G. Wardha
P.R. Pote Patil of this English medium self-financing High School (Classes 1 to 12)
Education and Welfare Rust, Camp Road, Amravati is under transfer of management.
The proposal received in the letter was under the consideration of the government.
The government's decision:
The school is managed by P. R. Pote Patil Education and Welfare Rust, Camp Road, Amravati.
The Government has decided to grant approval for the transfer to this institution on the following terms and conditions: -
(1) The condition of minimum marks of the school to which the management is transferred is relaxed for any reason.
Won't go.
(2) Any conditions of Government permission / approval in respect of the school to which the management has been transferred, and
Care should be taken not to change the conditions.
(3) Since the school is on the self-financing principle of English medium, the working teachers / non-teachers
The entire responsibility of the staff will rest with the organization that accepts the management transfer.
(4) From time to time, in respect of schools, teachers / non-teaching staff, salary / non-salary grants, students, etc. by the Government.
The new body will be bound to comply with the prescribed Acts, Rules, Orders, etc.
(5) This Management Transfer, Government Decision, Department of School Education and Sports, No: Mashah 2011 / (210/11)
MASHI-3 shall come into force in accordance with the rules and procedures prescribed on 17th February, 2012.
(6) The transfer of this management to the Government or to the field officers of the Department of Education.
If a complaint is received or it is found that there is a breach of the terms and conditions regarding the transfer of management
Government Decision Number: Mashah-3024 / Q. 323/24 SM-1
or the new allowances of the teaching / non-teaching staff working in the institution before the transfer of management.
In the event of a breach by the organization, the government will have the power to cancel the management transfer.
The Divisional Deputy Director of Education, Amravati Division, Amravati examined all the aspects and the above.
Further action on transfer of management of the school, including necessary conditions in addition to terms / conditions
Do it within 15 days and report it to the government.
The Government decision is available on the Government of Maharashtra website www.maharashtra.gov.in.
